  "response": "Yes, **money laundering** is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. It involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems, to make it appear as if it comes from lawful sources. \n\nMoney laundering is a serious criminal offense because it enables criminals to profit from illegal activities (such as drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or terrorism) while undermining the integrity of financial systems. Laws and regulations are in place globally to combat money laundering, and financial institutions are required to implement measures to detect and report suspicious activities.\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include **fines, imprisonment, and asset forfeiture**, and they vary depending on the jurisdiction and the severity of the offense.",
